OL,3,C'Major upgrade' to Met Office system
OL,4,Ccould help avoid flight delays
OL,6,F"Improvements in weather science
OL,7,Fbenefit us all, from more flights
OL,8,Frunning on time, to roads being
OL,9,Fgritted when they need to be, to
OL,10,Fenabling earlier preparations for
OL,11,Fstorms that risk lives and damage to
OL,12,Fhomes and businesses."
OL,14,FThe Met Office's director of science,
OL,15,FSimon Vosper, told a press briefing:
OL,16,F"We made a range of improvements,
OL,17,Ffirst and very topical at the moment
OL,18,Fis the UK's rainfall, so the quality
OL,19,Fof our rainfall forecasts has improved
OL,20,Fvery markedly.
